headline: Cadence’s (NASDAQ:CDNS) Q2 Sales Top Estimates, Stock Soars
summary: Semiconductor design software provider Cadence Design Systems (NASDAQ:CDNS) reported revenue ahead of Wall Street’s expectations in Q2 CY2025, with sales up 20.2% year on year to $1.28 billion. The company’s full-year revenue guidance of $5.24 billion at the midpoint came in 0.8% above analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.65 per share was 5.9% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
